name: which has irrevocably lost the idea of the "right side"
description:
Inspired by Oliver Sacks. 
One who has irrevocably lost the idea of the "right side." Both in relation to the world and to her own body. She takes her food only from the left side of the plate. She paints her lips and powders only on the left side, and does not even touch the right side of her face. Sometimes we lose a part of ourselves to life's various circumstances, but we gain new selves.  
Each of us is free to put his own meaning into his work, just as the viewer can put his own meaning into any art by any artist and give it his own meaning. This is one of the characteristics of art, it's versatility.
